ally in critically ill patients.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032645,0.070127,0.083529,0.094008,0.10077,0.10348,0.10271,0.096969,0.08931,0.090181,0.072809,0.063463],"unified_progress":[0.038829,0.067829,0.084327,0.093757,0.098125,0.10506,0.10212,0.099662,0.094025,0.088004,0.071926,0.056334]},{"section":11,"text":"The ultrasound findings of gallbladder wall thickening and pericholecystic fluid support cholecystitis.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034538,0.078627,0.090947,0.097576,0.096691,0.098704,0.097103,0.090067,0.1007,0.079683,0.070735,0.064626],"unified_progress":[0.036898,0.072721,0.091966,0.10505,0.10949,0.10489,0.10051,0.093739,0.09639,0.074237,0.061902,0.052204]},{"section":12,"text":"The pericholecystic fluid might indicate inflammation or even perforation.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031578,0.076863,0.091563,0.10056,0.099464,0.10089,0.098227,0.090444,0.098992,0.08097,0.069137,0.06131],"unified_progress":[0.032578,0.070418,0.092155,0.10651,0.11311,0.10635,0.10438,0.094809,0.095504,0.07472,0.05946,0.050001]},{"section":13,"text":"Since she's from a hospice setting, maybe she's had some recent illness or surgery that predisposes to acalculous cholecystitis.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036706,0.07442,0.082415,0.088602,0.095492,0.10557,0.098467,0.097441,0.09238,0.09233,0.075672,0.060502],"unified_progress":[0.088459,0.12026,0.10062,0.092474,0.08961,0.085515,0.083776,0.084756,0.077421,0.069479,0.059388,0.048241]},{"section":14,"text":"The confusion and fever could be systemic signs of infection, like sepsis from a gallbladder infection.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021949,0.05274,0.068038,0.081631,0.094023,0.1012,0.10777,0.10331,0.099747,0.097082,0.0927,0.079813],"unified_progress":[0.035811,0.051862,0.068152,0.071936,0.088531,0.093688,0.098781,0.10041,0.10339,0.10386,0.10067,0.082914]},{"section":15,"text":"Other possibilities?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029121,0.068318,0.088963,0.096097,0.096102,0.091951,0.0931,0.092245,0.090404,0.097147,0.081858,0.074693],"unified_progress":[0.031,0.064964,0.079342,0.093564,0.095126,0.095086,0.09657,0.097154,0.095606,0.099007,0.086412,0.066168]},{"section":16,"text":"Maybe a liver abscess, but the ultrasound would likely show that.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022616,0.059032,0.075932,0.085925,0.091624,0.096162,0.10248,0.10334,0.10506,0.098298,0.090706,0.068817],"unified_progress":[0.027094,0.059645,0.078289,0.092601,0.098683,0.09865,0.10169,0.10367,0.10314,0.09929,0.080798,0.056445]},{"section":17,"text":"Pancreatitis?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023778,0.058652,0.074173,0.084767,0.092877,0.098224,0.1033,0.10444,0.10385,0.099188,0.08927,0.067478],"unified_progress":[0.031482,0.062474,0.079715,0.091008,0.09832,0.10151,0.10336,0.1033,0.10095,0.096564,0.078485,0.052824]},{"section":18,"text":"But the symptoms and ultrasound don't point to that.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.01637,0.046377,0.063546,0.075388,0.085195,0.093184,0.10583,0.11177,0.11313,0.11137,0.10557,0.072262],"unified_progress":[0.023153,0.052404,0.069255,0.078341,0.092761,0.095226,0.10211,0.1112,0.11086,0.1185,0.092771,0.053421]},{"section":19,"text":"Pyelonephritis?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023157,0.056622,0.071452,0.082057,0.090711,0.097243,0.10296,0.10517,0.10553,0.10136,0.092263,0.071472],"unified_progress":[0.028017,0.060658,0.0776,0.088924,0.096392,0.10118,0.10282,0.10437,0.1033,0.098501,0.082462,0.055777]},{"section":20,"text":"The location is wrong.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.018607,0.049609,0.065814,0.076951,0.086014,0.093661,0.10447,0.10951,0.11145,0.10868,0.10279,0.072438],"unified_progress":[0